Yen Erases Gains as Rise to Postwar Record Boosts Intervention Speculation

-- B y   Y o s h i a k i   N o h a r a
-- 
2011-03-17T01:05:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/yen-erases-gains-as-rise-to-postwar-record-boosts-intervention-speculation.html
The yen erased gains after climbing
to a postwar high of 76.36 against the dollar, amid speculation
Japanese policy makers will intervene to weaken the currency.  The yen traded at 79.67 as of 10:02 a.m. in  Tokyo  from the
79.59 close yesterday in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
